Lesson 6 – Creating Basic Visualizations & Interactivity
1. Name three types of visuals you can create in Power BI.

Bar chart

Line chart

Pie chart

2. How do you add a slicer to a report?

Click the Slicer visual in the Visualizations pane and drag a field into it.

3. What is the difference between a bar chart and a column chart?

Bar chart shows data horizontally

Column chart shows data vertically

4. How do you change the color of a visual background?

Select the visual → Format pane → Background → Color.

5. What does "drill-down" mean in a visual?

Drill-down lets users click on a data point to see more detailed levels of data.

